The article expresses shock and sadness over a vicious attack on Salman Rushdie in New York. The author, along with Americans and people worldwide, prays for his recovery. The first responders and brave individuals who helped Rushdie are praised. Rushdie is described as someone who represents essential ideals such as truth, courage, resilience, and the ability to share ideas without fear. The article reaffirms the commitment to these values in solidarity with Rushdie and freedom of expression.